songs.title: OMG
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: All]
Oh my gosh, I did it again

[Verse 1: Jesy Nelson with Jade Thirlwall & Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
I don't even know how I did that
Need a round of applause
Just like cream to a kitty cat
Lining up at the door
Maybe it's the way I work it
My beach bring the boys to the shore
Maybe it's the way I flirt
That they get hurt, they just don't learn

[Pre-Chorus: Jade Thirlwall]
I don't even know why they fall like dominoes

[Chorus: All]
Oh my gosh, I did it again
He said I broke his heart, it keeps happening
I don't know why they always fall for me
Why they always fall for
Oh my gosh, I did it again
He said I broke his heart, it keeps happening
I don't know why they always fall for me
Why they always fall for

[Post-Chorus: All]
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah, oh
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah, oh

[Verse 2: Perrie Edwards & Jade Thirlwall]
Them boys getting too ambitious
They should win an award
Got twenty more, plenty more fishes
But I still come first
Maybe I'm superstitious
I want to break this curse
They say they want to lay it on me
I'm their one and only girl

[Pre-Chorus: All]
I don't even know why they fall like dominoes

[Chorus: All & Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
Oh my gosh, I did it again
He said I broke his heart, it keeps happening
I don't know why they always fall for me
Why they always fall for
Oh my gosh (Oh my gosh), I did it again
He said I broke his heart, it keeps happening
I don't know why they always fall for me
Why they always fall for

[Post-Chorus: All]
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah, oh
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah
Oh, na, nah, oh

[Bridge: All, Jade Thirlwall & Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
Oh my gosh, I think I did it again (Did it again)
Broke his heart, why does this keep happening? (Keep happening)
Don't come crying when I say it's the end (Say is the end)
I'm ringing the alarm, boy you better run on (Oh)

[Chorus: All]
Oh my gosh, I did it again
He said I broke his heart, it keeps happening
I don't know (Don't come crying when I say it's the end) why they always fall for me (I don't know why they always fall for me)
Why they always fall for (Always fall from me)

[Outro: Leigh-Anne Pinnock]
Oh my gosh
Oh my, oh my, oh, oh, oh, oh my
Oh my gosh
Oh my, oh my, oh, oh, oh, oh my
Oh my gosh
